Reasoning: The paper uses social media data to study human values and attitudes towards vaccination, which falls under the domain of social computing (cs.SI). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques to analyze the linguistic descriptions of Facebook pages, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper explores the potential of social media as a sensing tool, which could fall under cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also touches upon the societal and cultural factors that influence vaccine hesitancy, which could fall under social computing (cs.SOC) or software engineering (cs.SD) if the focus is on designing effective communication campaigns.
